==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*aitra-'', from Indo-European ''*oid-'' ‘to swell’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[ettor]], Old High German [[eitar]] (German [[Eiter]] ‘pus’), Old Norse [[eitr]] (Swedish [[etter]]).  The IE root was also the source of Greek {{polytonic|[[οἶδος]]}} ‘swelling’, Slavic ''jadъ'' (Russian [[яд]] ‘poson’).

